<br>
Very high level necros have a resurrection spell. The component to cast this spell is an &quot;essence stone.&quot; I think it may be a component for other necro spells as well.<br>
<br>
Essence stones are created using another spell called &quot;Sacrifice.&quot; The spell component for Sacrifice is an emerald. The necro targets a volunteer player character and casts Sacrifice. The volunteer gets a little prompt dialog like the one you get for resurrections. Once the volunteer agrees to it, they are killed and lose experience like any other death. This exp loss cannot be regained by ressing. For this, the necro gets an essence stone. <br>
<br>
I think the sacrificed victim must be level 45+. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 32nd Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#333333>(11/6/00 6:16:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=77.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Dont camp!  Kill!</span><hr size=1> Sure this is 45+ Nefarious? I thought it was 50+<br>
<br>
